                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill acknowledges receipt of department’s telegram and states that he
                    has just seen the minister for foreign affairs, who has asked him to inform
                    Secretary Root that his Government is profoundly humiliated and distressed at
                    the Lienchou occurrence, and <pb facs="0415" n="309" xml:id="pg_309"/> promised
                    prompt and vigorous action. Mr. Rockhill insisted with him on the close relation
                    between the boycott movement and the massacre, and that security for the United
                    States could not be insured without a complete suppression of the movement in
                    all shapes. The Emperor’s edict of November 2, if carried out, is good.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
